'''Kumaku Shrine''' (???????) is a {{ill|lt=shrine|Q845945|qid=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Nishio|Q317844|qid=Q317844|1=Nishio}}, {{ill|lt=Aichi Prefecture|Q80434|qid=Q80434|1=Aichi Prefecture}}. Its former shrine rank was {{ill|lt=G?-sha|Q134917316|qid=Q134917316|1=Gō-sha}}.

=== Overview ===
Its precincts are in {{ill|lt=Yatsumote-ch?|Q87701383|qid=Q87701383|1=Yatsuomote-chō}} Urai and {{ill|lt=Kumami-ch?|Q80930815|qid=Q80930815|1=Kumami-chō}}. The main hall in Yatsumote-ch? is a one-bay irimoya-zukuri structure with a three-bay front porch, built in {{ill|lt=1527|Q6412|qid=Q6412|1=1527}} (Daiei 7), and is a {{ill|lt=Important Cultural Property|Q1188622|qid=Q1188622|lt=national Important Cultural Property|1=Important Cultural Property (Japan)}}. It is an {{ill|lt=Engishiki naisha|Q11064932|qid=Q11064932|lt=Engishiki-listed shrine|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}. The enshrined deities are {{ill|lt=Emperor Nintoku|Q313119|qid=Q313119|lt=?sazaki-no-Mikoto|1=Emperor Nintoku}}, {{ill|lt=Susanoo|Q272993|qid=Q272993|lt=Susanoo-no-Mikoto|1=Susanoo-no-Mikoto}}, and {{ill|lt=Atsuta Shrine|Q482065|qid=Q482065|lt=Atsuta-no-?kami|1=Atsuta Shrine}}. It is said to have been founded in the era of Emperor Sujin.

